				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">atm they do not, and it seems only debuffs and dot's have had a major increase to how often they land, as well as the necro lifetap, while most other DD's seem resisted about the same, with only a very slight improvement, and believe it or not sk lifetaps are slighty easier to resist i think (i've had 2 partial resists out of 10 with around 500mr, where as before they'd all be full).
<br />

<br />
The only noticable change for mages is our pets actually resists some snares now, and roots last for an avg of 10 seconds or less if they land, but like i said this should have been implemented long ago.  Other than that i have no problem with my pet's defense, that's a pve issue, I dont even have a problem with the pet's offense at lower end, because they are quite mean if u're opponent is not twinked. When you start fighting necros with more hp than your earth pets, or rangers or any melees with a phylactery clicky who regen more than your pet can damage them, it gets frustrating.  A melee from ldon gear'd to GoD gear'd should have doubled his AC, and regen near 40 per tick. Our pets' offensive has not scaled as well in pvp.
<br />

<br />
Also, when looking at the standings on the boards, there are lots of unexplained reasons why some of the stats are the way they are.  I generally look more at total pts than total kills, because it gets rid of those 3k fungi twinks at lvl 20 running around PC.  But even that reading can be misinterpreted, Mass pvp MA's can have real high points, some people kill their own people if they get low so the pts stay in guild rather than to a rival guild, some classes are much harder to find a GoD grp with so are pvp active because they dont really have a choice, and fights are rarely 1 v 1, its usually /ran 50, /ran 50, whatever numbers pops, that's the numbers.
<br />

<br />
I have only seen 1 incident where someone purposefully trained others, then sneak in a kill shot while the mob is beatting away for those precious pts, and only heard of 3 other similar incidents. I think vz is also one of the *cleaner* zeks (the 3 top guilds look down upon training, most players wait till u finish your mob before atkin, blah blah), so not sure how its effectin the others, but instagate potions have definitely been used more often now, and book hugging is at its worst.
<br />

<br />
As you can tell, I'm not a major fan of the pt system, but pay close attention to it nontheless (ranked 29 in total pts last i checked), but when u come back u jus gotta try it out u'reself.  Again this is all jus my personal observations, you'd have to try it out yourself<br />_________________<br />Meetmefrend
<br />

<br />
Magician of Zephyros, Vallon Zek</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
